  "text": "The set of metabolic reactions included in the model is mathematically represented as a stoichiometric matrix S of size M * R , where M is the number of metabolites and R is the number of reactions included in the model. Given the stoichiometric matrix S , where each element s i ,j represents the stoichiometric coefficient of each metabolite within each reaction, the formulation of a FBA problem may be formulated in this way: The parsimonious FBA (pFBA) [CITATION_1] is a variant of the classic FBA approach that applies the same principles, but it set as objective function the minimization of the sum of all fluxes. Therefore, pFBA assumes that there is a selection for the fastest growing strains that minimize the total necessary resources to implement the optimal solution.",
